VW’s Skoda Plans to Launch New Model in 2012, Handelsblatt Says

-- B y   C h r i s t i a n   V i t s
-- 
2011-02-28T21:28:14Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-28/vw-s-skoda-plans-to-launch-new-model-in-2012-handelsblatt-says.html
Skoda Auto AS, the Czech unit of  Volkswagen AG , aims to launch a new model globally in 2012,
 Handelsblatt  reported, citing an interview with the company’s
Chief Executive Officer Winfried Vahland.  The so-called Global Compact Car may cost around 12,000
euros ($16,570) and would be designed as a five-seat sedan for
families, according to the report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Christian Vits in Frankfurt at 
 cvits@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Craig Stirling at   cstirling1@bloomberg.net  